set.name: Lockmaster's Armour (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most subtle of Arnorian scouts. Like shadows they carried out countless good works in the name of the City of Kings.

set.name: Armour of Forgotten Hope (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most respected Arnorian officers. Their inspiration led to countless victories for the peoples who dwelled in the City of Kings.

set.name: Armour of the Northern Star (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most valiant Arnorian soldiers. The might of these inspired countless legends, some of which are still remembered in the City of Kings.

set.name: Armour of the Arnorian Holdfast (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most tireless Arnorian defenders. These city-defenders served as a beacon of strength in the face of those who would do harm to the people of the City of Kings.

set.name: Armour of True Aim (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most skilled Arnorian archers. The arrows and bolts of these Men and Women fell upon the enemy in such number that they routed many enemies who assembled before the forces of the City of Kings.

set.name: Raiments of Long Memory (Max Level: 47)
set.description: These fine raiments were worn by the most wise Arnorian archivists. The forgotten majesty of Númenor was often recalled in the presence of these learned few who served the City of Kings.

set.name: Heartmender's Raiments (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most talented Arnorian bards. The songs of these gifted few were filled with beauty and strength in equal measures, the melodies of which could be heard often within the City of Kings.

set.name: Raiments of Vicious Proclamation (Max Level: 47)
set.description: These fine raiments were worn by the most persuasive Arnorian rune carvers. The words of these gifted orators were often enough to convince a villain to flee, rather than attempt to harm a citizen of the City of Kings.

set.name: Armour of the Oathesworn (Max Level: 47)
set.description: This fine armour was worn by the most dedicated Arnorian sentries. Tales tell of the oathes sworn on the shores of Evendim by these elite protectors of the City of Kings.
